<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,258,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,366,391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[301,383,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1540,1562]" captionTargetBox="[154,1432,610,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,587,1518]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 14. Argia tupi (Calvert) BRAZIL: Chapada dos Guimarães; ♀ (ACR 8184)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1250853/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[403,471,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Head.</emphasis>
Labium, labrum, clypeus, base of mandibles, genae, frons and front of head to level of antennae tan, epicranium black, except for small dark cupreous spots lateral to each lateral ocelli and at base of antennae, postocular spots tan, tan occipital bar separated from postocular spots by a thin black line, border of postocular lobes black; eyes (in life) black dorsally and white ventrally; rear of head largely black, a pale line bordering eye margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
